userStories.description:
As a developer, I need to fix the Module Federation RUNTIME-010 error so the store (and all other) micro-frontends load correctly in the host shell. The root cause is that MicroFrontendApp.tsx calls `init({ name: '@ecommerce-host', remotes: [...] })` inside the loadMicroFrontend async function (line 93). The host is already initialised by @nx/module-federation at build time with name 'host'; a second init() call with a different name is rejected by the MF runtime. The fix:
1. In `micro-frontends/host/src/microFe/MicroFrontendApp.tsx`:
   a. Remove `init` from the import on line 17; add `registerRemotes` (import { registerRemotes, loadRemote } from '@module-federation/runtime').
   b. Add a module-level Set above the component: `const registeredRemotes = new Set<string>();`
   c. Replace the `init({ name: ..., remotes: [...] })` block (lines 93-101) with:
      ```
      if (!registeredRemotes.has(microFrontendConfig.remoteName)) {
        registerRemotes([{ name: microFrontendConfig.remoteName, entry: `${remoteUrl}/remoteEntry.js` }]);
        registeredRemotes.add(microFrontendConfig.remoteName);
      }
      ```
2. Run `cd micro-frontends && npx tsc --noEmit -p host/tsconfig.app.json` to confirm typecheck passes.
